						<summary>

						<p>This is an incomplete inscription recording a gift of cows for “half” a perpetual lamp in the temple by one Śelvappiḷḷai <hi rend="italic">alias</hi> Śīyagaṅ[gaṉ] of Kūṟṟaṅguḍi (a quarter) of Panaippākkam in Uvaṟūr-nāḍu, who is called a <hi rend="italic">Durai-araiśarmudali</hi> of Kuṇḍalūr. </p>						

						</summary>
